table-wrap.anchoringText: Individual wells were completed across three to six reservoir zones as shown in Table 1, below. The STMZGP system’s annular flow screens consisted of 6” solid base pipe with the 125 micron woven-wire screen raised off the base pipe to provide screen ID=6.366” and Screen OD=7.440”. This design resulted in a flow annulus of 3.555 square inches between the 6” base pipe and the screen ID. Flow was able to move down this annulus to the production sleeve where it could be isolated or allowed to flow into the base pipe.
